-- Factbox: Berkshire Hathaway at a glance
-- 
-- Wed Apr 28, 2010 2:59pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/04/28/us-berkshire-buffett-company-idUSTRE63R4AJ20100428

 

 (Reuters) - Berkshire Hathaway Inc ( BRKa.N ) 

 ( BRKb.N ), the insurance and investment company run by billionaire Warren Buffett, will hold its annual shareholder meeting on Saturday in Omaha, Nebraska. The meeting attracted 35,000 people last year. Along with the annual meeting for Wal-Mart Stores Inc, it is one of the most heavily anticipated and attended galas in corporate America, drawing investors and media from all over the world. Buffett, 79, took over Berkshire in 1965 when it was a struggling textile mill. Berkshire owns roughly 80 companies and has a market value of about $189 billion, Reuters data show. For a preview of the annual meeting, please click